<section class="section">
    <h2>Smart Lighting Buying Guide</h2>
    
    <h3>Smart Bulbs vs Smart Switches</h3>
    <div class="grid grid-2 mb-4">
        <div class="card">
            <h4>Smart Bulbs</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Easy installation - just screw in</li>
                <li>Individual bulb control</li>
                <li>Color changing options available</li>
                <li>Work with existing switches</li>
                <li>Replace when they burn out</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4>Smart Switches</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Control any bulb type</li>
                <li>Wall switch control maintained</li>
                <li>One switch controls multiple bulbs</li>
                <li>Requires electrical installation</li>
                <li>Long-term solution</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Key Features to Consider</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Connectivity:</strong> WiFi direct, hub-required, or Bluetooth options</li>
        <li><strong>Color Options:</strong> White only, tunable white, or full color spectrum</li>
        <li><strong>Brightness:</strong> Measured in lumens - higher is brighter</li>
        <li><strong>Dimming:</strong> Smooth dimming capabilities</li>
        <li><strong>Voice Control:</strong> Alexa, Google Assistant, Siri compatibility</li>
        <li><strong>Scheduling:</strong> Automated on/off times and scenes</li>
        <li><strong>Energy Efficiency:</strong> LED smart bulbs use 75% less energy</li>
    </ul>
</section>

